reviews.review_text:
Not a bad audience recording. Sounds good on the pc speakers at least. It improves greatly after the first song.

Could this be the best Yellow Dog story ever? The band vamps "Heart And Soul" for two and a half minutes while Bobby tells the story in a rapid fire pace, then they finish the joke with a big flourish!

It sounds to me like there are NO transitions between Truckin' and He's Gone nor between He's Gone and Sugar Magnolia. Clear stops and starts.

Also, where are the SBD leftovers? Grateful Dead download series (Volume 10) only has 6 songs; You Win Again, Bird Song, Playing In The Band, Morning Dew, Uncle John's Band, One More Saturday Night.

Can't the rest of the show be posted as a SBD?

Peace, Bob
